-- Investec's Co-Head of Credit Jeffrey Burch to Leave Firm After 12 Months
-- Kate Haywood
-- 2010-06-24T11:18:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/investec-s-co-head-of-credit-jeffrey-burch-to-leave-firm-after-12-months.html

          
          
             Jeffrey Burch , formerly co-head of
credit at Investec Asset Management, will leave at the end of
June to pursue other opportunities after 12 months at the
company.  
 Theodore Stamos , who helps oversee around $70 billion of
assets at the firm, will replace Burch and run the credit unit
alongside  Simon Howie , Investec said in an e-mailed statement.  
 Burch joined Investec from Blue Mountain Capital, a
specialist credit hedge fund, in June 2009. Burch was not
immediately available for comment.  
